cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfUgs.name: cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfUgs
cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfUgs.description: This object indicates the number of static UGS service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfUgsad.name: cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfUgsad
cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfUgsad.description: This object indicates the number of static UGS-AD service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfRtps.name: cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfRtps
cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfRtps.description: This object indicates the number of static RTPS service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfNrtps.name: cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfNrtps
cdxCmtsUscbStaticSfNrtps.description: This object indicates the number of static NRTPS service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbDynSfBe.name: cdxCmtsUscbDynSfBe
cdxCmtsUscbDynSfBe.description: This object indicates the number of dynamic BE service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbDynSfUgs.name: cdxCmtsUscbDynSfUgs
cdxCmtsUscbDynSfUgs.description: This object indicates the number of dynamic UGS service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbDynSfUgsad.name: cdxCmtsUscbDynSfUgsad
cdxCmtsUscbDynSfUgsad.description: This object indicates the number of dynamic UGS-Ad service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbDynSfRtps.name: cdxCmtsUscbDynSfRtps
cdxCmtsUscbDynSfRtps.description: This object indicates the number of dynamic RTPS service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbDynSfNrtps.name: cdxCmtsUscbDynSfNrtps
cdxCmtsUscbDynSfNrtps.description: This object indicates the number of dynamic NRTPS service flows which use this upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsUscbDescr.name: cdxCmtsUscbDescr
cdxCmtsUscbDescr.description: This object indicates the description of upstream channel bonding group.

cdxCmtsCmOnOffNotification.name: cdxCmtsCmOnOffNotification
cdxCmtsCmOnOffNotification.description: This notification indicates that the cable modem coming online and going offline. A notification will be sent from CMTS for a cable modem status changing to online or offline within the interval specified in cdxCmtsCmOnOffTrapInterval.

cdxCmtsCmChOverNotification.name: cdxCmtsCmChOverNotification
cdxCmtsCmChOverNotification.description: This notification is sent at the completion of a CMTS channel override operation if cdxCmtsCmChOverTrapOnCompletion is true in the original entry. Once a channel override operation has been activated, it cannot be stopped. That is, it will run until either the CMTS has generated downstream frequency and/or upstream channel override fields in the RNG-RSP message sent to a cable modem or cdxCmtsCmChOverTimeExpiration time expired. In either case, the operation is completed. State in the cdxCmtsCmChOverState object will tell in which condition the operation is completed.

cdxCmtsCmDMICLockNotification.name: cdxCmtsCmDMICLockNotification
cdxCmtsCmDMICLockNotification.description: This notification is sent whenever a modem is locked because it failed the Dynamic Message Integrity Check.

cdxWBResilRFDown.name: cdxWBResilRFDown
cdxWBResilRFDown.description: This notification indicates that a RF channel changed state to logical DOWN state.

cdxWBResilRFUp.name: cdxWBResilRFUp
cdxWBResilRFUp.description: This notification indicates that a RF channel changed state to logical UP state.

cdxWBResilCMPartialServiceNotif.name: cdxWBResilCMPartialServiceNotif
cdxWBResilCMPartialServiceNotif.description: This notification indicates that a Cable Modem is in partial service. Object docsIfCmtsCmStatusDownChannelIfIndex represents the target wideband/narrowband ifindex.

cdxWBResilCMFullServiceNotif.name: cdxWBResilCMFullServiceNotif
cdxWBResilCMFullServiceNotif.description: This notification indicates that a Cable Modem is recovered from partial service. Object docsIfCmtsCmStatusDownChannelIfIndex represents the target wideband/narrowband ifindex.

cdxWBResilEvent.name: cdxWBResilEvent
cdxWBResilEvent.description: This notification indicates that a wideband resiliency event is received by CMTS.
